 The record in these cases shows that it took significant periods of training and experience for operators to learn the standardized techniques utilized by B&L Ireland and by B&L Hong Kong to assemble sunglasses ready for sale to the ultimate consumers. Even Dr. Cohen admitted that certain problems encountered by B&L Ireland and by B&L Hong Kong might have been attributable to the fact that they were mass producing sunglasses, rather than assembling prescription eyeglasses for a retail optical shop.
